data.name: StressGenePred
data.description: Stress predicting framework with microarray data based on CMCL and logical correlation model

evidence: The README describes running scripts directly: `python learn.py ...`, `python test.py ...`, indicating it is an end-user analysis program rather than a library.
The tool performs domain-specific analysis: "Stress Predictor based on Machine Learning" and includes "GSEA (Gene set enrichment test) Testing", directly generating scientific analysis outputs.
Installation/usage is via cloning and running Python scripts; there is no mention of PyPI, containers, or other registries, implying distribution via the source repository.
